Write the constructor method in the Face class.
Remember to respond with a snippet in the form of the following:
```
class Face {
    constructor(edges, surface) {
        // your code here
    }
}
```

```
class Face {
    constructor(edges, surface) {
        if (!edges || !Array.isArray(edges) || edges.length === 0) {
            throw new Error('Face must have at least one edge.');
        }
        if (!surface) {
             throw new Error('Face must have a surface.');
        }
        this.edges = edges;
        this.surface = surface;
    }
}
```
